1
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:18,321
[1927]

2
00:01:39,817 --> 00:01:41,440
Are you done?

3
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:45,090
Please stay still, Miss. I'm almost done.

4
00:01:47,390 --> 00:01:48,391
All done.

5
00:02:00,057 --> 00:02:01,400
Wow! I'm quite a pretty girl.

6
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:06,560
So pretty. My girl is the prettiest.

7
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,520
What is the point of getting dolled up when nobody can see me?

8
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:11,320
I've never left my house.

9
00:02:14,223 --> 00:02:15,880
Who is here, Lang? Let's go and have a look.

10
00:02:16,350 --> 00:02:19,240
Please don't go! Your dad could scold you.

11
00:02:19,450 --> 00:02:20,451
This way, sir.

12
00:02:37,477 --> 00:02:40,440
Lang, who is he?

13
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,760
He is Lord Sampanpanich, he works for the ministry.

14
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,640
Why did you ask?

15
00:02:51,123 --> 00:02:52,800
I'm visiting your place quite often.

16
00:02:53,270 --> 00:02:55,880
But I've never asked if you're annoyed by my company.

17
00:02:58,063 --> 00:02:59,600
How could I be?

18
00:02:59,950 --> 00:03:01,560
You're talking about business with my dad.

19
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:03,880
I've done talking about business with him a while ago.

20
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:08,200
I keep visiting your place because of something else.

21
00:03:14,063 --> 00:03:16,920
What is this tree called? I like its fruits.

22
00:03:18,590 --> 00:03:21,290
This is pomegranate tree, a lucky tree.

23
00:03:21,877 --> 00:03:23,280
Its fruits produce many seeds.

24
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:25,240
We believe that planting this tree

25
00:03:25,343 --> 00:03:26,560
will bring plenty of children to house owners.

26
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,540
If that so,

27
00:03:30,723 --> 00:03:32,800
I think I should plant the tree at my house.

28
00:03:35,483 --> 00:03:39,120
Will it be alright if I ask for the seed from your house to plant at mine?

29
00:03:41,237 --> 00:03:42,238
Well…

30
00:03:43,337 --> 00:03:44,480
I'm not sure.

31
00:03:45,670 --> 00:03:47,040
The pomegranate tree belongs to my dad.

32
00:03:47,617 --> 00:03:49,618
You should ask him.

33
00:03:51,383 --> 00:03:53,200
If he allows it,

34
00:03:54,923 --> 00:03:57,080
will the expert of pomegranate come to live at my house?

35
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:18,240
I wish both of you to grow old together and live happily.

36
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,880
When you marry my son,

37
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,841
you need to love him dearly.

38
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:40,240
I've never known anything about love.

39
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,820
What does it like?

40
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:46,160
I will teach you, Shen.

41
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:57,400
This painting is called…

42
00:04:57,920 --> 00:04:58,921
Make Love.'

43
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,801
Make Love?'

44
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:05,521
Make love...

45
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:09,280
is an action of affirmation to show true love among two people.

46
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:25,801
Don't be scared.

47
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:28,121
Just follow my lead.

48
00:05:28,710 --> 00:05:30,320
I will take it slow.

49
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,442
Thank you

50
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,520
for teaching me about love.

51
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,760
I think I will miss you so much.

52
00:06:58,943 --> 00:07:00,680
We just got married

53
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:03,080
and next week we will be apart.

54
00:07:05,310 --> 00:07:06,792
I really don't want to go to Penang.

55
00:07:08,850 --> 00:07:10,590
Don't say that.

56
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:14,360
It's the government work and you can't avoid it.

57
00:07:15,843 --> 00:07:19,440
One more thing, we haven't been apart yet.

58
00:07:22,037 --> 00:07:23,600
My mom used to tell me that

59
00:07:25,343 --> 00:07:28,000
we need to spend every moment as memorable

60
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:32,880
as possible before we are deemed to part.

61
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:36,924
You're right.

62
00:07:41,683 --> 00:07:42,684
In that case,

63
00:07:44,623 --> 00:07:45,750
before I leave,

64
00:07:46,943 --> 00:07:48,360
I will love you every day.

65
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:50,441
And we…

66
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:53,720
will be happy together.

67
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:48,601
Please wait for me,

68
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:52,640
I will come back and make love to you every night.

69
00:10:47,130 --> 00:10:49,280
I've told you a million times that you can't make sound when you eat.

70
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:53,081
When you were at your house,

71
00:10:53,510 --> 00:10:55,640
was it necessary to eat like you were starving your whole life?

72
00:10:56,150 --> 00:10:57,320
Watch your manners.

73
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,000
I'm sorry, Mother.

74
00:11:00,857 --> 00:11:04,000
It's been three months already and there is no sign for Perm to return.

75
00:11:04,877 --> 00:11:06,001
You must be so lonely.

76
00:11:07,157 --> 00:11:08,842
You can come and hang out with me if you like.

77
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,441
You can talk to me about anything.

78
00:11:14,037 --> 00:11:15,760
Try some Massaman curry.

79
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:17,401
I can get it for you.

80
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:19,220
Term, didn't you forget?

81
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,280
Shen doesn't eat soup curry.

82
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:23,720
She is worried that it could upset her stomach.

83
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,241
Am I right, Shen?

84
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:27,481
- I…
- What?

85
00:11:27,843 --> 00:11:29,360
You've been living in this house for so long

86
00:11:29,517 --> 00:11:30,600
and you haven't tried curry?

87
00:11:32,317 --> 00:11:33,640
This is a Thai family household.

88
00:11:33,757 --> 00:11:35,758
If you don't eat curry, what can you eat?

89
00:11:36,957 --> 00:11:40,040
We won't cook you the food that you're familiar with

90
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:43,120
because we are not fond of Chinese food.

91
00:11:47,110 --> 00:11:49,120
Why don't you try spicy shrimp paste?

92
00:11:49,492 --> 00:11:51,760
If my brother comes home and he sees you getting slimmer,

93
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:54,000
he would be mad at us for not taking good care of you.

94
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:56,000
Thank you.

95
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,121
But…

96
00:11:58,323 --> 00:12:00,760
actually I can eat some curry and coconut milk soup.

97
00:12:01,337 --> 00:12:03,480
Well, isn't it great?

98
00:12:03,757 --> 00:12:04,758
Let me give you some.

99
00:12:07,250 --> 00:12:08,251
Oh my!

100
00:12:12,937 --> 00:12:13,938
Rayrai!

101
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:25,551
Thank you.

102
00:12:25,783 --> 00:12:26,784
Watch out, it could burn.

103
00:12:28,297 --> 00:12:31,200
Look at that, you just made a couple get mad at each other.

104
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:34,000
But I didn't do anything.

105
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:35,401
Don't talk back to me.

106
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,400
My elder brother is not around.

107
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,360
I need to take care of his wife for him.

108
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,400
What is wrong with you? Why are you getting jealous?

109
00:13:12,857 --> 00:13:13,858
Should I get jealous?

110
00:13:14,130 --> 00:13:15,720
Shen just moved in

111
00:13:15,943 --> 00:13:18,000
and you were trying to please her more than

112
00:13:18,044 --> 00:13:19,045
pleasing me for a whole year.

113
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:22,057
Women are so overthinking. This is so annoying.

114
00:13:22,410 --> 00:13:23,411
Where are you going?

115
00:13:26,060 --> 00:13:27,061
To hang out with Shen,

116
00:13:28,843 --> 00:13:29,844
isn't it great?

117
00:13:30,257 --> 00:13:32,750
Term! She is your sister-in-law.

118
00:13:33,190 --> 00:13:35,820
You need to behave. Don't be so gross.

119
00:13:37,471 --> 00:13:38,472
Rayrai!

120
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:39,840
You need to lower your jealousy with me.

121
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,601
I think I keep you full all the time.

122
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:45,920
Or your desire is higher than others?

123
00:13:48,163 --> 00:13:49,164
If you want some,

124
00:13:49,757 --> 00:13:50,787
I can give it to you.

125
00:14:11,683 --> 00:14:12,760
Or you don't want it anymore?

126
00:16:31,177 --> 00:16:34,160
Aunt Somsong prepared you a bigger bowl today.

127
00:16:34,630 --> 00:16:37,161
But I can feed you only little bites, please don't get bored before I'm done.

128
00:16:42,123 --> 00:16:43,124
Should I

129
00:16:43,757 --> 00:16:45,722
feed you bigger bites instead?

130
00:16:50,417 --> 00:16:51,960
I'm joking.

131
00:16:56,217 --> 00:16:57,218
Little bite.

132
00:17:06,902 --> 00:17:08,160
Hello, this is Pipatratsada residence.

133
00:17:12,303 --> 00:17:13,840
You've learned how to prepare fruits for months,

134
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:17,280
and you still haven't done it properly.

135
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:20,120
I pushed the knife too deep?

136
00:17:22,797 --> 00:17:24,080
When your mom was still around,

137
00:17:24,458 --> 00:17:26,760
hasn't she passed on any knowledge about homemaking skills?

138
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:30,840
Or your kind only know about slaughtering ducks and chickens?

139
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:35,040
You don't eat fruits so you don't know how to prepare them properly?

140
00:17:38,767 --> 00:17:41,760
So you don't want it anymore?

141
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:43,840
I can share it with kitchen staffers.

142
00:17:45,590 --> 00:17:47,400
Khunying.

143
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,320
Someone from the ministry just called to inform you that

144
00:17:50,390 --> 00:17:52,160
your son will come home in two days.

145
00:17:52,637 --> 00:17:53,800
- Really?
- That's right.

146
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,201
Perm, my dear.

147
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:57,880
You need to go to the kitchen

148
00:17:58,030 --> 00:17:59,960
and tell them to prepare Perm's favorite dishes.

149
00:18:00,031 --> 00:18:01,032
Okay.

150
00:18:15,783 --> 00:18:16,800
Where are you rushing to?

151
00:18:17,270 --> 00:18:18,271
To the kitchen.

152
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:22,920
Are you really lonely lately?

153
00:18:27,157 --> 00:18:28,240
What are you talking about?

154
00:18:30,297 --> 00:18:32,940
I saw you sneak up on us last night.

155
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:45,720
If that is what you really want,

156
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:47,921
I can give it to you.

157
00:18:48,830 --> 00:18:49,831
Term,

158
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:51,680
I am your sister-in-law.

159
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:54,680
Stop saying something disgusting like this already.

160
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:56,361
Why's that?

161
00:18:58,397 --> 00:19:00,360
My brother has been away for three months now.

162
00:19:03,403 --> 00:19:04,520
It's fine if you get lonely.

163
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:09,120
Even if I get lonely, I wouldn't trouble you with that for sure.

164
00:19:09,960 --> 00:19:13,080
Besides, someone at the ministry called to let us know that

165
00:19:13,637 --> 00:19:15,720
your brother will be home in two days.

166
00:19:42,630 --> 00:19:43,760
Hello, honey.

167
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,640
Your favorite steamed rice dumplings.

168
00:19:51,417 --> 00:19:53,168
I learned to make it when you were away.

169
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,241
So tasty.

170
00:20:08,637 --> 00:20:11,400
Do you remember Tone, Soi's son, who used to work here?

171
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:13,481
Sure, I do.

172
00:20:14,203 --> 00:20:17,497
I heard that her whole family moved to Penang.

173
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:19,480
Did you get to meet him?

174
00:20:19,880 --> 00:20:22,480
I did, he seemed like a hard-working guy.

175
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:24,400
So I recruited him to work here.

176
00:20:25,250 --> 00:20:27,320
- He will be here next week.
- What position?

177
00:20:27,997 --> 00:20:29,550
We don't have any job for him at the moment.

178
00:20:29,983 --> 00:20:32,120
I hired him to be Shen's personal driver.

179
00:20:36,497 --> 00:20:39,440
Hey, I ordered a car from Italy, just for you.

180
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:41,961
Honey?

181
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:46,962
Shen is not that busy, she doesn't need her own car.

182
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:49,920
I think it's way too much for her

183
00:20:50,390 --> 00:20:52,320
- to have her own personal driver.
- That's right.

184
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,550
I still need to ride a tricycle taxi to work every day.

185
00:20:55,520 --> 00:20:57,760
Since you bought the car already,

186
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,700
I think we should use it as a family car.

187
00:21:00,283 --> 00:21:01,480
I can use it in the morning for work,

188
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:04,120
and Tone can drive Mom and Rayrai

189
00:21:04,161 --> 00:21:05,162
for some errands later.

190
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:08,160
- What do you think, Mom?
- Great idea.

191
00:21:08,293 --> 00:21:09,880
I bought this car with my own money.

192
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:12,080
I also paid Tone from my own pocket.

193
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:15,081
Shen will be the one who can use these.

194
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:20,600
What? Can't you share the car with me? I'm your brother.

195
00:21:22,070 --> 00:21:23,071
Share?

196
00:21:24,077 --> 00:21:27,078
I'm an eldest son.

197
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:30,400
I've shared everything with you my whole life,

198
00:21:31,910 --> 00:21:33,100
but not this time, I won't.

199
00:21:34,830 --> 00:21:37,743
On the other hand, have you ever shared anything with me?

200
00:21:44,630 --> 00:21:45,800
Am I right, Little Nualnoy?

201
00:22:04,950 --> 00:22:05,951
Father?

202
00:22:06,930 --> 00:22:08,520
Look who's here with me?

203
00:22:13,690 --> 00:22:14,691
Hello, Father.

204
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:23,400
I heard that my wife was the one feeding you every day.

205
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:25,081
Do you like her?

206
00:22:29,480 --> 00:22:32,320
I'm glad to see both of you get along really well.

207
00:23:10,363 --> 00:23:11,520
A penny for your thoughts?

208
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,240
Nothing in particular, dear.

209
00:23:20,250 --> 00:23:21,251
About the car,

210
00:23:21,937 --> 00:23:24,360
I think it'd be a great idea to share it with the family.

211
00:23:25,257 --> 00:23:27,240
I don't normally need it to go anywhere.

212
00:23:30,270 --> 00:23:32,160
I bought you a car and you denied it?

213
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:34,440
You don't really need it but you can still have it.

214
00:23:35,263 --> 00:23:37,920
You're Lord Sampanpanich's wife and you need something to show, okay?

215
00:23:51,350 --> 00:23:52,680
Your return

216
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:56,440
is the greatest gift that I could ask for.

217
00:24:02,623 --> 00:24:03,920
I missed y…

218
00:24:08,743 --> 00:24:10,040
Are you alright?

219
00:24:11,240 --> 00:24:14,141
I was just worried about work tomorrow.

220
00:24:15,950 --> 00:24:17,523
I haven't been to the ministry for three months.

221
00:24:17,672 --> 00:24:19,680
I'm not sure about how it will go.

222
00:24:22,043 --> 00:24:23,044
You should go to bed first.

223
00:24:25,350 --> 00:24:27,120
- But I…
- I told you to go to bed.

224
00:24:50,497 --> 00:24:51,520
Please wait for me,

225
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:54,200
I will come back and make love to you every night.

226
00:25:13,923 --> 00:25:17,440
[Chanting.]

227
00:25:17,524 --> 00:25:19,637
[Chanting.]

228
00:25:19,870 --> 00:25:22,500
[Chanting.]

229
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:26,160
[Chanting.]

230
00:25:47,703 --> 00:25:50,320
Tone! You're here!

231
00:25:50,510 --> 00:25:51,511
Hello, sir.

232
00:25:51,790 --> 00:25:53,200
How are you? Are you exhausted?

233
00:25:53,503 --> 00:25:55,320
Not at all, sir. I slept all the way

234
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,700
from Hat Yai to Hua Lamphong.

235
00:25:56,801 --> 00:25:59,920
Good. What about the car? Any trouble at all?

236
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:02,040
It's in good shape. The mechanic checked it already.

237
00:26:02,983 --> 00:26:03,984
Good.

238
00:26:04,557 --> 00:26:06,560
- Come here.
- Yes, sir.

239
00:26:06,910 --> 00:26:08,040
- Come here.
- Yes, sir.

240
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:12,137
This is Shen, my wife. She will be your new boss.

241
00:26:16,320 --> 00:26:17,920
Nice to meet you, Ms. Shen.

242
00:26:18,243 --> 00:26:20,800
No need to be formal. We're around the same age.

243
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:24,440
This is Tone. He will be your personal driver.

244
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:30,760
See? Isn't my wife so pretty?

245
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:34,401
Yes, sir.

246
00:26:45,910 --> 00:26:47,960
You're all grown up now, Tone. So big.

247
00:26:49,757 --> 00:26:51,560
Let me see your face closer.

248
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:56,360
You're as good-looking as your dad.

249
00:26:57,423 --> 00:26:59,080
How are your parents?

250
00:26:59,643 --> 00:27:01,280
Mom has some medical conditions.

251
00:27:01,570 --> 00:27:03,080
Other than that, she's doing well.

252
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:06,200
Good. I'm glad you're working for us.

253
00:27:06,777 --> 00:27:10,280
Even though, you're not working for me directly.

254
00:27:12,650 --> 00:27:15,320
- Shen is such a lucky girl.
- Mom!

255
00:27:24,763 --> 00:27:26,700
I can guarantee you that she won't recognize you for sure.

256
00:27:28,457 --> 00:27:30,870
Auntie, look who's here with me?

257
00:27:30,883 --> 00:27:31,884
Who?

258
00:27:32,343 --> 00:27:34,000
Hello, Aunt Somsong.

259
00:27:34,723 --> 00:27:37,240
You look so familiar but I can't recall.

260
00:27:38,303 --> 00:27:40,720
I'm Tone, Soi's son.

261
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:45,500
What? You're Tone? You're all grown up now.

262
00:27:46,710 --> 00:27:48,720
And you're handsome just like an actor from a live soap opera.

263
00:27:51,110 --> 00:27:51,611
I see.

264
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:53,480
Tone will be living with us.

265
00:27:53,630 --> 00:27:56,040
Mr. Perm hired him to be Ms. Shen's personal driver.

266
00:27:56,283 --> 00:27:57,284
That's great.

267
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:59,540
The more the merrier, kid.

268
00:27:59,757 --> 00:28:02,640
Tone, this is Duang. He is Mr. Perm's personal driver.

269
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:04,880
They are Noy and Prapai.

270
00:28:05,123 --> 00:28:06,024
Hello, nice to meet you.

271
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:08,600
Tone, can you tell us more about Penang?

272
00:28:08,700 --> 00:28:10,080
Did you live close to the beach?

273
00:28:10,570 --> 00:28:12,590
He is exhausted from all the traveling. Let him rest.

274
00:28:12,803 --> 00:28:15,640
Let's go. I'll take you to our room, you're sharing it with me.

275
00:28:15,717 --> 00:28:16,718
- Nice.
- Let's go.

276
00:28:17,217 --> 00:28:19,218
Tone, when you're done, please come here and hang out with me.

277
00:28:21,850 --> 00:28:22,851
Let's go.

278
00:28:42,957 --> 00:28:43,958
Thank you.

279
00:28:45,303 --> 00:28:48,240
I've never thought that I would get a gift this huge.

280
00:28:48,810 --> 00:28:49,811
It's just a car.

281
00:28:54,623 --> 00:28:55,624
Well..

282
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:58,720
should we ride around the city?

283
00:28:59,363 --> 00:29:01,280
You can test the new car.

284
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:03,041
I'm busy tomorrow.

285
00:29:19,757 --> 00:29:20,758
Or…

286
00:29:22,522 --> 00:29:24,560
should we go to Bang Saen next week?

287
00:29:33,650 --> 00:29:35,200
Just like when we first got married…

288
00:29:36,457 --> 00:29:37,477
You should go there by yourself if you want to.

289
00:29:37,843 --> 00:29:39,440
I gave you a car, I hired a personal driver for you.

290
00:29:40,080 --> 00:29:41,081
What more do you want?

291
00:29:43,117 --> 00:29:44,840
- I…
- I'm going to bed. I'm tired.

292
00:30:13,017 --> 00:30:15,440
Nothing has changed in the past 10 years.

293
00:30:16,403 --> 00:30:17,903
Except us, we are growing.

294
00:30:18,017 --> 00:30:19,560
I still remember us

295
00:30:19,677 --> 00:30:21,640
skinny dipping and jumping in the river.

296
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:26,801
Tone, do you want to reenact my memory?

297
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:29,160
Should we jump in the river to cool us down?

298
00:30:29,277 --> 00:30:30,400
You crazy? No way.

299
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:32,440
People can see us, that would be so embarrassing.

300
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:35,720
You lived abroad for more than 10 years.

301
00:30:36,057 --> 00:30:37,360
You must have used only foreign language.

302
00:30:37,950 --> 00:30:40,920
When you speak Thai, it sounds weird.

303
00:30:42,437 --> 00:30:45,000
Yeah, I guess you're right.

304
00:30:45,163 --> 00:30:46,600
Hey, Tone!

305
00:30:47,400 --> 00:30:49,080
- What do you mean by that?
- Huh?

306
00:30:49,163 --> 00:30:51,120
It's not like that. You got it all wrong.

307
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:52,520
- Are you sure?
- Yup.

308
00:30:57,223 --> 00:30:58,224
Hey, Shin.

309
00:30:58,760 --> 00:31:00,120
Can I ask you something?

310
00:31:00,597 --> 00:31:02,080
- Shoot.
- About Ms. Shen.

311
00:31:02,400 --> 00:31:03,700
What is she like?

312
00:31:06,203 --> 00:31:08,400
I will work for her so I know how to behave.

313
00:31:09,477 --> 00:31:12,377
Well, at first glance,

314
00:31:12,703 --> 00:31:15,080
she looked so pitiful.

315
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:18,400
Then I took a second glance, I saw her eyes

316
00:31:18,810 --> 00:31:21,480
and she was like that woman who hides her stubbornness.

317
00:31:24,283 --> 00:31:25,284
And…

318
00:31:26,810 --> 00:31:30,040
what's the deal between Mr. Perm and Ms. Sern?

319
00:31:31,137 --> 00:31:33,200
Deal? Like what?

320
00:31:33,410 --> 00:31:35,640
- They're married couple.
- I know, but…

321
00:31:35,830 --> 00:31:38,560
Do they really love each other?

322
00:31:39,397 --> 00:31:41,080
Or is it just an arranged marriage?

323
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:44,000
Nope, not arranged marriage for sure.

324
00:31:44,510 --> 00:31:46,120
Mr. Perm chose his own wife.

325
00:31:47,120 --> 00:31:49,040
Ms. Shen is a daughter of a Chinese businessman.

326
00:31:49,497 --> 00:31:52,160
Mr. Perm fell in love with her when he visited her dad's house.

327
00:31:53,243 --> 00:31:55,030
He really loves his wife.

328
00:31:55,423 --> 00:31:57,880
- Don't you dare doing something nasty to her.
- Come on!

329
00:31:59,240 --> 00:32:01,800
Who would dare? She is my boss' wife.

330
00:32:03,270 --> 00:32:04,910
Why do you have to be be so mad about it?

331
00:32:08,663 --> 00:32:09,664
Let's go to sleep.

332
00:32:13,277 --> 00:32:14,278
What?

333
00:32:33,910 --> 00:32:37,000
Then she grabbed Laothong's arm,

334
00:32:37,483 --> 00:32:40,560
Khunpaen yelled to stop, and raised his hands to protect.

335
00:33:08,940 --> 00:33:09,941
Shen,

336
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:14,321
where are you going?

337
00:33:14,883 --> 00:33:16,480
I think I will visit my place for a bit.

338
00:33:16,500 --> 00:33:17,822
I haven't been to my home for a while.

339
00:33:18,510 --> 00:33:19,880
This is your place.

340
00:33:21,023 --> 00:33:24,000
You're married to this family. What other places are you going to visit?

341
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:26,280
I need to talk to my dad.

342
00:33:26,630 --> 00:33:28,560
Khunphra was fed already.

343
00:33:28,677 --> 00:33:30,160
It won't be long. I will be back soon.

344
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:34,960
I know that you don't have to run errands.

345
00:33:35,517 --> 00:33:39,000
You just want to show off your new car to people.

346
00:33:40,770 --> 00:33:42,480
I won't allow you to go.

347
00:33:45,643 --> 00:33:47,363
Don't you hear it? You can't go.

348
00:33:48,483 --> 00:33:49,577
Go back to the kitchen.

349
00:33:49,650 --> 00:33:51,423
Help Erb prepare for lunch. Go!

350
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:57,081
Okay.

351
00:34:06,170 --> 00:34:07,171
Tone.

352
00:34:07,703 --> 00:34:08,604
Yes, ma'am.

353
00:34:08,640 --> 00:34:10,400
- Can you give me a ride to my house?
- Sure.

354
00:34:12,240 --> 00:34:13,960
Where is it, ma'am?

355
00:34:14,150 --> 00:34:15,760
Talat Noi. I'll tell you where.

356
00:34:15,963 --> 00:34:16,964
Sure, ma'am.

357
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:24,670
If you love yourself and you feel embarrassed, then you need to stop.

358
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:28,920
Don't cause a scene or you will be mortified.

359
00:34:29,723 --> 00:34:31,320
If you don't listen…

360
00:34:33,210 --> 00:34:34,211
Right.

361
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:37,801
Is that a car?

362
00:34:37,983 --> 00:34:38,984
I think so.

363
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:14,920
Who told you that you could read this romance novel?

364
00:35:15,150 --> 00:35:16,131
Why can't I?

365
00:35:16,143 --> 00:35:18,800
It's nothing but love story. Why are you reading it?

366
00:35:19,160 --> 00:35:20,640
- I…
- I will burn it.

367
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:22,520
If I find out that

368
00:35:22,630 --> 00:35:24,520
you continue reading it,

369
00:35:24,880 --> 00:35:26,400
I will flog you so bad.

370
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:28,881
Dad!

371
00:35:30,897 --> 00:35:31,898
Miss?

372
00:35:41,120 --> 00:35:45,000
My teacher said that it was just a book about young people's love.

373
00:35:45,477 --> 00:35:47,680
Why didn't my dad forbid me from reading it?

374
00:35:48,903 --> 00:35:51,240
Can't I know anything about love?

375
00:35:52,550 --> 00:35:54,480
If you dad won't let you read it,

376
00:35:54,597 --> 00:35:56,160
then you should listen to him.

377
00:35:57,320 --> 00:35:58,720
If you want to know about love,

378
00:35:59,362 --> 00:36:03,320
someone will teach you all about it one day.

379
00:36:25,743 --> 00:36:26,744
Thank you.

380
00:36:27,250 --> 00:36:30,760
- Ms. Shen!
- Lang!

381
00:36:32,290 --> 00:36:34,452
You can park the car over there.

382
00:36:34,710 --> 00:36:35,711
Okay.

383
00:36:36,617 --> 00:36:38,960
Sir, look who is here?

384
00:36:39,530 --> 00:36:41,400
Shen? Why are you here?

385
00:36:42,610 --> 00:36:44,160
I'm visiting you, Dad.

386
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:46,000
I've been away for months,

387
00:36:46,090 --> 00:36:48,320
you're not going to ask me how I am doing?

388
00:36:52,630 --> 00:36:54,000
You look fine to me.

389
00:36:55,043 --> 00:36:56,960
Are you behaving well?

390
00:36:57,044 --> 00:36:58,600
Did you cook for them?

391
00:36:58,843 --> 00:37:01,280
I did. But they don't eat Chinese food.

392
00:37:01,423 --> 00:37:02,800
So I need to learn to cook Thai food.

393
00:37:03,077 --> 00:37:05,320
Good. Just learn whatever they want you to.

394
00:37:05,443 --> 00:37:06,480
Don't cross them

395
00:37:06,943 --> 00:37:08,600
or it could affect my business.

396
00:37:13,263 --> 00:37:14,760
All you care about is your business?

397
00:37:15,397 --> 00:37:19,080
That's right. What else should I care about?

398
00:37:29,398 --> 00:37:31,600
People in that place hurt your feeling again, didn't they?

399
00:37:33,837 --> 00:37:35,257
My poor baby.

400
00:37:35,810 --> 00:37:37,760
Your dad never shows his love to you

401
00:37:38,642 --> 00:37:40,600
and your new family keeps pushing you.

402
00:37:42,120 --> 00:37:45,360
But your husband is home now, it will get better, right?

403
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:49,760
I thought it would be like that

404
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:53,240
but since he got back

405
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:56,400
he hasn't been the same.

406
00:37:57,360 --> 00:37:59,520
What? What is going on?

407
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:02,400
He bought me so many things,

408
00:38:03,150 --> 00:38:05,960
including the car and my personal driver.

409
00:38:08,130 --> 00:38:09,760
Still, he hasn't been the same.

410
00:38:14,497 --> 00:38:15,498
Well…

411
00:38:16,350 --> 00:38:17,351
I mean…

412
00:38:17,717 --> 00:38:20,120
did you fulfill your duty as a wife?

413
00:38:20,680 --> 00:38:21,760
That could be the reason if you didn't.

414
00:38:37,080 --> 00:38:39,681
Please don't be shy.

415
00:38:39,917 --> 00:38:41,160
This is totally normal.

416
00:38:45,683 --> 00:38:49,520
On the contrary, when I tried to be closer to him,

417
00:38:49,977 --> 00:38:51,680
he kept pushing me away.

418
00:38:52,357 --> 00:38:53,358
What?

419
00:38:54,690 --> 00:38:57,080
I tried to make us be happy together

420
00:38:57,600 --> 00:38:59,400
like before he was sent off to Penang.

421
00:39:05,640 --> 00:39:09,000
We were so happy on daily basis back then.

422
00:39:19,200 --> 00:39:21,440
He taught me about love.

423
00:39:32,240 --> 00:39:33,560
When he was back,

424
00:39:35,240 --> 00:39:36,590
it seemed like he didn't want it anymore.

425
00:39:39,710 --> 00:39:40,711
This is weird.

426
00:39:41,750 --> 00:39:44,360
When the man just got married,

427
00:39:44,751 --> 00:39:45,920
his desire would occur so often.

428
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:50,840
What about you?

429
00:39:51,677 --> 00:39:52,760
What about your drive?

430
00:39:59,617 --> 00:40:01,480
This is completely normal.

431
00:40:04,650 --> 00:40:05,720
Of course, I want to do it.

432
00:40:10,757 --> 00:40:11,758
Can you get me this set?

433
00:40:13,070 --> 00:40:14,071
Please wait.

434
00:40:18,337 --> 00:40:19,497
Just try the recipe.

435
00:40:19,890 --> 00:40:22,440
You boiled it for your dad all the time.

436
00:40:22,823 --> 00:40:25,200
If your husband's blood and pressure flows better,

437
00:40:25,743 --> 00:40:27,920
things will get better eventually.

438
00:40:30,810 --> 00:40:33,100
You think it's because of his exhaustion from work, right?

439
00:40:34,490 --> 00:40:36,600
It's not because he isn't in love with me anymore, right?

440
00:40:38,103 --> 00:40:39,520
Don't say that.

441
00:40:40,163 --> 00:40:42,240
Why would be stop loving you?

442
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:48,280
Let me carry it, ma'am.

443
00:40:49,200 --> 00:40:50,000
Thank you.

444
00:40:53,177 --> 00:40:56,063
Are you hungry? I can hear your stomach.

445
00:40:57,560 --> 00:40:58,561
Nope.

446
00:41:00,277 --> 00:41:02,560
I saw a noodles shop over there. It looked good.

447
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:06,000
If you're hungry, you should get something to eat.

448
00:41:07,830 --> 00:41:08,831
It's fine.

449
00:41:09,997 --> 00:41:12,400
If you don't eat when it's time, it will hurt your stomach.

450
00:41:18,160 --> 00:41:20,520
Gastritis is hard to cure.

451
00:41:29,110 --> 00:41:31,000
I'll wait for you there.

452
00:41:31,910 --> 00:41:32,911
You're not hungry?

453
00:41:35,457 --> 00:41:36,458
I…

454
00:41:37,330 --> 00:41:39,277
You can sit with me and eat, I don't mind.

455
00:41:41,977 --> 00:41:42,978
Okay.

456
00:41:54,303 --> 00:41:55,304
Why are you smiling?

457
00:41:56,640 --> 00:41:57,641
It's nothing, ma'am.

458
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:00,200
I also slurp like this at home.

459
00:42:00,760 --> 00:42:02,960
You should try, it makes the food taste better.

460
00:42:14,390 --> 00:42:15,690
You're right. It does taste better.

461
00:42:21,920 --> 00:42:24,920
So you're close to Perm since you were young?

462
00:42:26,903 --> 00:42:28,200
I was born in this house.

463
00:42:29,043 --> 00:42:31,080
Mr. Perm and Mr. Term are a little bit older than me.

464
00:42:32,337 --> 00:42:33,680
We played together since we were kids.

465
00:42:34,850 --> 00:42:36,680
But I'm closer to Mr. Perm.

466
00:42:37,283 --> 00:42:39,040
Mr. Term liked to tease me.

467
00:42:41,720 --> 00:42:43,880
Khunphra and Khunying adored me as well.

468
00:42:45,470 --> 00:42:49,280
They raised you? That's why you are so polite and neat.

469
00:42:50,613 --> 00:42:53,760
Actually, I'm not that neat.

470
00:42:54,720 --> 00:42:56,280
I was a stubborn kid growing up.

471
00:42:57,270 --> 00:42:58,271
Were you?

472
00:43:00,070 --> 00:43:01,171
One time,

473
00:43:01,937 --> 00:43:04,560
Mr. Perm and I played in the rice field.

474
00:43:09,630 --> 00:43:11,640
We played in mud and it was all over our bodies.

475
00:43:16,663 --> 00:43:19,840
When we went home, his mom whipped me so bad.

476
00:43:21,497 --> 00:43:22,920
What is wrong with you?

477
00:43:23,323 --> 00:43:25,280
Why did you play in mud like that?

478
00:43:25,720 --> 00:43:27,800
How could you let Perm play with you like this?

479
00:43:28,960 --> 00:43:31,320
- She whipped you?
- That's right.

480
00:43:32,760 --> 00:43:35,080
You must be a stubborn kid for sure.

481
00:43:36,690 --> 00:43:37,840
Like a little monkey, ma'am.

482
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:52,440
Do you know a place where I can boil some soup for my husband?

483
00:43:53,410 --> 00:43:55,680
I think Mother will make a big fuss

484
00:43:56,190 --> 00:43:57,920
if I try to cook it at home.

485
00:43:58,703 --> 00:44:00,080
And my dad will get suspicious

486
00:44:00,690 --> 00:44:02,000
if I go back to his house.

487
00:44:04,130 --> 00:44:05,880
What type of soup is that?

488
00:44:06,743 --> 00:44:08,080
It's for nourishing his body.

489
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:11,120
He seems a little tired lately.

490
00:44:11,937 --> 00:44:14,920
It's Chinese herbal remedy and I can't cook it at home.

491
00:44:15,137 --> 00:44:16,600
Mother will get so mad.

492
00:44:20,097 --> 00:44:22,080
I think I know a place.

493
00:44:45,760 --> 00:44:47,160
Whose cottage is this?

494
00:44:47,603 --> 00:44:48,920
Can we use it?

495
00:44:49,680 --> 00:44:52,680
Khunphra owns this land and he rents it for farmers to plant rice.

496
00:44:53,383 --> 00:44:55,242
Nobody is living in the cottage.

497
00:44:55,600 --> 00:44:58,200
They will be here during harvesting and planting seasons.

498
00:44:59,183 --> 00:45:00,880
I ran around this place when I was a kid.

499
00:45:03,077 --> 00:45:04,078
This way, ma'am.

500
00:45:26,743 --> 00:45:28,080
The kitchen is in the back.

501
00:45:43,937 --> 00:45:44,938
Here it is.

502
00:45:47,443 --> 00:45:50,200
I will take you to the temple next time.

503
00:45:50,403 --> 00:45:51,720
Good, let's go.

504
00:45:52,880 --> 00:45:54,520
Shen hasn't come back yet?

505
00:46:30,320 --> 00:46:31,720
Ms. Shen, please drink some water.

506
00:46:32,583 --> 00:46:33,584
Thanks.

507
00:46:45,063 --> 00:46:47,240
You seem so happy to live with Mr. Perm.

508
00:46:47,477 --> 00:46:48,800
Why did you move?

509
00:46:49,880 --> 00:46:52,760
My dad worked for the store that imported products from Penang.

510
00:46:53,710 --> 00:46:56,720
When I was 11 years old, his boss wanted to move back.

511
00:46:57,240 --> 00:47:00,280
So he took my mom and I along to Penang.

512
00:47:02,760 --> 00:47:05,640
You must be so good at speaking English since you were there for years.

513
00:47:06,923 --> 00:47:08,240
I spoke English at school every day.

514
00:47:09,270 --> 00:47:10,560
But I spoke Thai when I was home.

515
00:47:13,317 --> 00:47:15,240
Is it hard? To speak English.

516
00:47:15,897 --> 00:47:17,200
Can you teach me later?

517
00:47:18,737 --> 00:47:21,510
I want to…

518
00:47:21,957 --> 00:47:23,520
speak English.

519
00:47:25,263 --> 00:47:27,200
Really? It's not that hard.

520
00:47:27,717 --> 00:47:28,718
I can teach you.

521
00:47:30,760 --> 00:47:31,920
It seems like it's going to be hard for me.

522
00:47:42,350 --> 00:47:44,440
Ms. Shen, are you okay?

523
00:47:54,183 --> 00:47:55,184
Ms. Shen?

524
00:48:39,723 --> 00:48:42,000
This is nothing, it will get better.

525
00:48:43,530 --> 00:48:44,531
Okay.

526
00:48:46,962 --> 00:48:49,640
I think I will walk around a little bit.

527
00:48:50,477 --> 00:48:51,800
Can you watch it for me?

528
00:48:52,183 --> 00:48:55,080
If the water is lower to half the pot, then you can stop.

529
00:48:55,640 --> 00:48:56,320
Got it, ma'am.

530
00:50:58,603 --> 00:50:59,604
Where were you?

531
00:51:00,317 --> 00:51:02,360
I told you not to go anywhere.

532
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:04,521
What is in the pot?

533
00:51:05,877 --> 00:51:08,480
I went outside and cooked soup for my husband.

534
00:51:08,868 --> 00:51:10,280
He seems a little tired lately.

535
00:51:10,803 --> 00:51:13,000
I won't let my son eat any Chinese food.

536
00:51:13,983 --> 00:51:15,120
Shin, throw it away.

537
00:51:16,360 --> 00:51:17,880
I said to throw it way.

538
00:51:18,840 --> 00:51:19,841
Yes, ma'am.

539
00:51:24,560 --> 00:51:25,600
I'm sorry.

540
00:51:32,480 --> 00:51:33,840
Follow me.

541
00:51:38,183 --> 00:51:39,800
Hey, you need to park it properly.

542
00:51:41,520 --> 00:51:42,521
Let's go.

543
00:51:47,450 --> 00:51:49,080
I know that I disobeyed you.

544
00:51:49,477 --> 00:51:51,160
But I didn't do anything wrong.

545
00:51:51,450 --> 00:51:53,040
Let me decide if it was right or wrong.

546
00:51:54,057 --> 00:51:55,762
I am a master of this house.

547
00:51:56,310 --> 00:51:57,640
If one of you won't listen to me,

548
00:51:57,963 --> 00:51:59,960
how can I control the rest of the house.

549
00:52:02,040 --> 00:52:04,760
You disobeyed me and you will be punished.

550
00:52:05,240 --> 00:52:06,241
Turn around.

551
00:52:06,857 --> 00:52:07,858
Khunying.

552
00:52:08,550 --> 00:52:10,170
I am the one who drove her around.

553
00:52:10,677 --> 00:52:11,920
It's my fault.

554
00:52:12,370 --> 00:52:13,680
Please punish me instead.

555
00:52:14,560 --> 00:52:15,683
Your boss ordered you to driver her around.

556
00:52:16,017 --> 00:52:17,600
You followed her order.

557
00:52:17,890 --> 00:52:19,363
I won't punish you, just go.

558
00:52:19,510 --> 00:52:22,040
If that's the case, I am her personal driver,

559
00:52:22,423 --> 00:52:24,760
- please punish me instead.
- Tone!

560
00:52:25,150 --> 00:52:26,151
Leave!

561
00:52:27,190 --> 00:52:28,360
I told you to leave.

562
00:52:31,370 --> 00:52:32,371
Yes, ma'am.

563
00:52:35,383 --> 00:52:37,640
If you wish to whip me, just do so. Let's get it over with.

564
00:52:38,917 --> 00:52:40,243
Don't challenge me.

565
00:52:47,090 --> 00:52:48,091
You're home, sir.

566
00:52:51,430 --> 00:52:52,431
I'm home?

567
00:52:53,863 --> 00:52:55,040
Watch out, sir.

568
00:53:03,083 --> 00:53:05,642
Mother? What is going on?

569
00:53:07,240 --> 00:53:08,600
Why did you punish my wife like this?

570
00:53:08,960 --> 00:53:11,920
She disobeyed me and left the house.

571
00:53:12,520 --> 00:53:15,000
I expected her to help me in the kitchen and she was gone.

572
00:53:16,897 --> 00:53:17,898
Mother.

573
00:53:18,990 --> 00:53:20,400
Shen is one of your help.

574
00:53:20,840 --> 00:53:23,320
She is my wife. If she doesn't want to be in the kitchen,

575
00:53:23,680 --> 00:53:25,800
then you can't make her go to the kitchen.

576
00:53:27,523 --> 00:53:29,240
Perm?

577
00:53:29,783 --> 00:53:30,784
Hey!

578
00:53:31,440 --> 00:53:33,840
You can't behave like this to me when you're drunk.

579
00:53:35,110 --> 00:53:36,111
Mother.

580
00:53:37,360 --> 00:53:40,737
I bought her car and I hired a driver for her,

581
00:53:41,337 --> 00:53:43,040
because she can go anywhere that she likes.

582
00:53:43,163 --> 00:53:44,840
Why did you stop her?

583
00:53:49,163 --> 00:53:50,164
Everyone.

584
00:53:50,463 --> 00:53:51,520
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

585
00:53:52,723 --> 00:53:55,400
You all need to leave Shen alone, you hear me?

586
00:53:55,577 --> 00:53:56,700
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

587
00:54:00,677 --> 00:54:01,840
Shen is my wife.

588
00:54:02,597 --> 00:54:05,400
And I want her to be the happiest girl in this house.

589
00:54:07,397 --> 00:54:08,398
Perm?

590
00:54:09,200 --> 00:54:10,921
Why are you so rude to me?

591
00:54:11,737 --> 00:54:14,120
You're too obsessed with your wife and you're ignoring me?

592
00:54:15,000 --> 00:54:16,001
Perm?

593
00:54:20,517 --> 00:54:22,360
You can go anywhere that you want.

594
00:54:22,423 --> 00:54:23,560
Don't listen to her.

595
00:54:24,277 --> 00:54:25,720
Let Tone take you.

596
00:54:27,440 --> 00:54:28,840
You're too drunk.

597
00:54:43,210 --> 00:54:44,211
I..

598
00:54:45,110 --> 00:54:47,320
I will get some damp cloth to clean you.

599
00:54:57,483 --> 00:54:58,984
It's too hot.

600
00:57:20,883 --> 00:57:21,884
Shen.

601
00:57:23,477 --> 00:57:25,080
Do you miss me?

602
00:57:26,490 --> 00:57:27,491
Of course, I do.

603
00:57:29,680 --> 00:57:31,440
I've always missed you.

604
00:58:17,183 --> 00:58:19,360
What are you trying to do?

605
00:58:20,080 --> 00:58:21,001
What are you doing?

606
00:58:21,030 --> 00:58:23,480
- I..I was just…
- Don't do it again next time.

607
00:58:28,120 --> 00:58:30,520
- But I..
- I said don't do it!

608
00:58:37,397 --> 00:58:38,398
Make love...

609
00:58:39,630 --> 00:58:42,560
is an action of affirmation to show true love among two people.

610
00:58:44,583 --> 00:58:46,320
You are the one who taught me this.

611
00:58:46,743 --> 00:58:49,320
- When you came back…
- Listen to me!

612
00:58:53,010 --> 00:58:54,440
I will do it with you

613
00:58:55,743 --> 00:58:56,800
whenever I want to.

614
00:58:57,560 --> 00:58:59,320
And we will not talk about this anymore.

615
01:01:15,880 --> 01:01:18,440
There will be a party at my boss' palace.

616
01:01:18,603 --> 01:01:19,840
I will take you to the party.

617
01:01:24,200 --> 01:01:25,260
Is it the gown?

618
01:01:25,301 --> 01:01:28,560
I can guarantee you that Ms. Shen will be the prettiest girl in the party.

619
01:01:29,400 --> 01:01:31,360
But I think it can be more beautiful.

620
01:01:33,680 --> 01:01:35,960
If there is anything I can do on behalf of Mr. Perm,

621
01:01:36,323 --> 01:01:37,760
please let me know.

622
01:01:41,857 --> 01:01:43,520
Sir, I heard that

623
01:01:43,563 --> 01:01:45,560
you just came back from Penang, didn't you?
